<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03090b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03090b">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03090b"> 90(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Lex Adamnani / (697) prev. women / from war (Columcille)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <font color="green">[Adamnan]</font> seems to have been the influential figure at the Parliament of Tara held in <mark>697</mark> and caused to be reenacted <mark>a law exempting women from fighting</mark>, which Columcille had caused to be passed, but which the passions of the time had disregarded. From that date the edict was strictly enforced and came to be known as the <mark>Lex Adamnani</mark> <small> Benedict Fitzpatrick, <a name="BFIM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BFIM"><cite title="source">Ireland and the Making of Britain</cite></a> (1922) 152</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
